## UniqueDocParamNames

**Severity:** error | **Type:** LiquidHtml

This check ensures that all `@param` entries in a `{% raw %}{% doc %}{% endraw %}` tag have unique names. Duplicate parameter names in a `{% raw %}{% doc %}{% endraw %}` block are always a mistake — only one declaration would be effective, and the duplication causes confusion for readers and tooling.

## Examples

### &#x2717; Incorrect Code Example (Avoid using this):

```liquid
{% raw %}
{% doc %}
  @param {string} title - The card title
  @param {string} title - Duplicate title param
  @param {string} description - The card description
{% enddoc %}
{% endraw %}
```

`title` is declared twice.

### &#x2713; Correct Code Example (Use this instead):

```liquid
{% raw %}
{% doc %}
  @param {string} title - The card title
  @param {string} description - The card description
{% enddoc %}
{% endraw %}
```

## Configuration

The default configuration for this check:

```yaml
UniqueDocParamNames:
  enabled: true
  severity: error
```

## Disabling This Check

Disabling this check is not recommended. Duplicate parameter names are always a mistake.

